  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6775 sitting 6 points below the GEX flip at 6781, dealers are currently in long gamma mode and likely buying this dip as expected in the PIN regime. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+8.9B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally, while the negative gamma at 6770 (-5.3B) provides a floor where dealers become forced buyers. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading in the narrow 6770-6781 range suggests dealers are actively stabilizing price action through contra-trend hedging.\n\nKey levels: Watch for rejection at 6780-6785 (heavy positive gamma) and support at 6770 where dealer buying should intensify.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect rangebound trading between 6770-6800 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
